Use of Password-Based Message
Authentication Code 1 (PBMAC1) in PKCS
#12 Syntax
2024", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="This document specifies additions and amendments to RFCs 7292 and 8018.  It defines a way to use the Password-Based Message Authentication Code 1 (PBMAC1), defined in RFC 8018, inside the PKCS #12 syntax.  The purpose of this specification is to permit the use of more modern Password-Based Key Derivation Functions (PBKDFs) and allow for regulatory compliance.", style=filled, fillcolor=green, fontsize=18, penwidth=3, fontweight=bold]; 

